workflow.name: Automate menstrual cycle tracking with GPT-4, Google Sheets and Telegram notifications
workflow.description:
## Who's it for

Women and healthcare providers who want to automate menstrual cycle tracking with personalized AI-powered health insights delivered through multiple channels.

## What it does

This workflow automates the complete cycle tracking process:
- Retrieves period and symptom data from Google Sheets every morning
- Analyzes patterns using OpenAI GPT to generate personalized health insights
- Sends daily notifications via Telegram on weekdays
- Creates Google Calendar reminders for upcoming cycle events
- Generates comprehensive weekly reports sent via email on weekends

## How it works

1. **Daily Trigger**: Activates every morning at 8 AM
2. **Data Collection**: Fetches period tracking and symptom logs from Google Sheets
3. **AI Analysis**: GPT-4 analyzes your cycle data to provide personalized insights and predictions
4. **Smart Distribution**: Weekday updates go to Telegram for quick access, weekend summaries are emailed
5. **Calendar Integration**: Automatically creates events for predicted cycle phases

## Requirements

- Google account (for Sheets and Calendar)
- Telegram account and bot token
- OpenAI API key
- Gmail account for email reports

## Setup steps

1. Configure the "Configuration Settings" node with your personal IDs
2. Connect your Google Sheets with period and symptom data
3. Set up Telegram bot and add your chat ID
4. Add OpenAI credentials for AI analysis
5. Connect Gmail for weekly reports
6. Activate the workflow

## How to customize

- Adjust trigger time to your preferred schedule
- Modify AI prompts for different health focuses
- Add more notification channels (Slack, Discord, etc.)
- Customize report formatting and frequency
- Add additional data sources for more comprehensive tracking

parameters.content:
# üå∏ Menstrual Cycle Intelligence Hub - AI Integrated

## What This Template Does

This workflow automates menstrual cycle tracking with AI-powered health insights delivered through multiple channels. It retrieves period and symptom data from Google Sheets every morning, analyzes patterns using OpenAI GPT to generate personalized health insights, sends daily notifications via Telegram on weekdays, creates Google Calendar reminders for upcoming cycle events, and generates comprehensive weekly reports sent via email on weekends.

## Who It's For

Women and healthcare providers who want to automate menstrual cycle tracking with personalized AI-powered health insights delivered through multiple channels.

## How It Works

1. **Daily Trigger**: Activates every morning at 8 AM
2. **Data Collection**: Fetches period tracking and symptom logs from Google Sheets
3. **AI Analysis**: GPT-4 analyzes your cycle data to provide personalized insights and predictions
4. **Smart Distribution**: Weekday updates go to Telegram for quick access, weekend summaries are emailed
5. **Calendar Integration**: Automatically creates events for predicted cycle phases

## Requirements

- Google account (for Sheets and Calendar)
- Telegram account and bot token
- OpenAI API key
- Gmail account for email reports

## Setup Steps

1. Configure the "Configuration Settings" node with your personal IDs
2. Connect your Google Sheets with period and symptom data
3. Set up Telegram bot and add your chat ID
4. Add OpenAI credentials for AI analysis
5. Connect Gmail for weekly reports
6. Activate the workflow

## How to Customize

- Adjust trigger time to your preferred schedule
- Modify AI prompts for different health focuses
- Add more notification channels (Slack, Discord, etc.)
- Customize report formatting and frequency
- Add additional data sources for more comprehensive tracking

## üìÖ Step 1: Schedule Trigger

This node triggers the workflow every day at 8 AM.

**To customize:**
- Change the trigger hour to your preferred time
- Add multiple trigger times if needed
- Consider your timezone settings

## ‚öôÔ∏è Step 2: Configuration

**IMPORTANT: Update these values:**

1. `sheetsDocumentId`: Your Google Sheets ID
2. `periodSheetName`: Name of your period data sheet
3. `symptomSheetName`: Name of your symptom log sheet
4. `telegramChatId`: Your Telegram chat ID
5. `userEmail`: Your email address
6. `calendarId`: Usually 'primary'

## üìä Step 3: Data Collection

**Google Sheets Structure:**

**Period Data Sheet:**
- Start Date
- End Date
- Flow Level (light/medium/heavy)
- Cycle Length

**Symptom Log Sheet:**
- Date
- Symptoms (mood, cramps, etc.)
- Energy Level
- Notes

## ü§ñ Step 4: AI Analysis

**OpenAI analyzes:**
- Cycle regularity patterns
- Symptom correlations
- Next period prediction
- Ovulation window estimation
- Personalized health recommendations

**Note:** Uses GPT-4 for best accuracy

## üîÄ Step 5: Smart Routing

**Logic:**
- **Weekend** ‚Üí Generate weekly summary ‚Üí Send email report
- **Weekday** ‚Üí Send daily update ‚Üí Create calendar event

This ensures you get quick daily updates during the week and comprehensive summaries on weekends.

## üìß Weekend Branch

**Weekly Email Report includes:**
- 7-day cycle summary
- Symptom trends analysis
- Health recommendations
- Upcoming predictions
- Lifestyle tips for next week

## üí¨ Weekday Branch

**Daily Updates via:**
1. **Telegram**: Instant notifications with today's insights
2. **Google Calendar**: Creates reminders for predicted events 7 days ahead

Perfect for staying informed without information overload!

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
